  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1943 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The frameless leaflet features a photograph of two persons – an elder man wearing a dark suit, a dark bow tie and a white shirt, and a young dark-haired woman wearing a red dress with a white lace collar and short lace sleeves. He is looking up to her; she is looking down at him. In the lower section of the picture, the Serbo-Croatian title ‘Njegova druga mladost’ (His second youth) is printed in a red field. The German original film title was ‘Altes Herz wird wieder jung’ (An old heart becomes young again).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Emil Jännings and Maria Landrock played the leading roles. The film was directed by Erich Engel and released in 1943.</ab>
